<HEADLINE>
PICKUP POSSIBLY USED BY ESCAPED KILLER AND PRISON GUARD IS FOUND 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MATT STEARNS  
 c. 1999 Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. -- The pickup truck thought to have been used
in the October disappearance of a convicted murderer and a prison
guard was found near Joplin, Mo., investigators said Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities are searching the 1989 Ford F-150 for clues to the
whereabouts of Terry Banks, the killer, and Lynette Barnett, the
corrections officer who authorities think helped Banks escape from
the Crossroads Correctional Center in Cameron, Mo., on Oct. 29.
</P>
<P>
   The truck was sold by relatives of Banks for about $2,000 to a
woman near Joplin on Nov. 18, said FBI agent Kurt Lipanovich, who
is working on the case. Authorities found the truck Dec. 3.
</P>
<P>
   ``She's just an innocent third party in this,'' Lipanovich said
of the truck's buyer, whom he would not identify.
</P>
<P>
   Lipanovich would not say whether Banks' relatives would be
charged in connection with the case.
</P>
<P>
   Some of Barnett's belongings were found in the truck, said
Lipanovich. He would not describe the items.
</P>
<P>
   Barnett's mother, Faye Moots, said she had not been told what
items were found in the truck.
</P>
<P>
   ``I certainly hope this means there's a breakthrough,'' Moots
said, ``that there's hope she may come back alive.''
</P>
<P>
   Barnett had cashed her $1,400 paycheck in a Kansas City, Mo.,
liquor store the night of the disappearance.
</P>
<P>
   ``This gives us a direction of travel,'' Lipanovich said.
</P>
<P>
   Lipanovich said the couple probably were driving another
vehicle, but authorities didn't know what it could be.
</P>
<P>
   Banks, 26, was convicted of first-degree murder in 1995 and was
serving a life term without parole. The murder occurred in Rocky
Comfort, Mo., just southeast of where the truck was found. Banks
lived in southwest Missouri when he killed Tim Eastburn on Nov. 19,
1992.
</P>
<P>
   Banks is white, 6 feet tall and weighs about 190 pounds. He has
fair skin, red hair and hazel eyes. He has several tattoos,
including a Tasmanian devil on his left arm and the Roman numeral
IV on his left hand. He has a scar on his right hand and a scar
from a stab wound on his chest.
</P>
<P>
   Barnett, 27, is white, with green eyes and red hair that may be
dyed blonde. She is 5 feet 5 inches tall and weighs about 120
pounds.
</P>
<P>
   The pair will be featured on the television show ``America's
Most Wanted'' tonight.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
