nation's top Internet-access provider are reportedly in talks about
forming a far-reaching alliance to market each others' products and
services. By Leslie Kaufman.
</P>
<P>
   FRANCE-MCDONALDS (Paris) _ The culture war occasioned by the
presence of McDonald's restaurants in France has continued with a
campaign of full-page newspaper ads in which the company that
operates McDonald's restaurants in France takes a potshot at
Americans and the questionable sources of their food
_hormone-treated beef, genetically modified crops and mass-produced
vegetables. By John Tagliabue.
</P>
<P>
   WEB-PATENTS _ All over the Internet, from the most popular
search engines to personal home pages, are buttons that offer to
send users to an online store, where they can buy books or music or
other merchandise. Hundreds of thousands of sites have added these
links because they earn commissions if any of their users click on
them and then buy something. This week, all of those sites were put
on notice that they might be violating a patent just granted to a
New York company called Linkshare. By Saul Hansell.
</P>
