<SLUG> BC-HKN-NHLWEST12-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Potvin on the block
 &HT;    By Jeff Schultz
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Anybody who saw Felix Potvin give up a goal on a clear
50-foot slap shot by the Thrashers' Mike Stapleton might conclude
the Islanders goalie has lost it.
</P>
<P>
   But rumors that Vancouver general manager Brian Burke is
pursuing Potvin have merit. The Canucks are believed to be offering
the No. 1 pick that they acquired from Florida as part of the Pavel
Bure trade and goalie Garth Snow. The Islanders will take the pick
but would prefer a young forward over Snow.
</P>
<P>
   One thing is certain: Snow doesn't like being the yo-yo in trade
talks. ``I like being in Vancouver. I thought I made great strides
last year. I'm definitely better this year and I know I can make
that jump to the next level. I don't mean to sound cocky or
arrogant but I know I can make it to the next level.''
</P>
<P>
   RULES OF THE ROAD
</P>
<P>
   The night before every road game, a member of the Los Angeles
coaching staff slips a scouting report under each player's hotel
room door. Something is working. The Kings have an 8-4-3 road
record. Last season, they were 14-25-2 on the road.
</P>
<P>
   ``All of training camp, I really keyed on that first game in
Nashville (Tenn.),'' coach Andy Murray said. ``All through camp we
had Nashville signs all over the dressing room. We had their lineup
up about 10 days before the game. This was a measuring stick for
our team. We wanted to be a harder working team. Last year, they
outworked us and beat us three times. We felt that might be as
important a game as we played all year.''
</P>
<P>
   MARSHMALLOW MAN
</P>
<P>
   Chicago's Tony Amonte, on owning the second-longest active
playing streak in the league (192 games, behind Phoenix's Teppo
Numminen's 326): ``It must be the body. It's chiseled out of
marshmallows.'' . . .
</P>
<P>
   The continued absence of injured defensive specialist Jere
Lehtinen has led Dallas coach Ken Hitchcock to stopping matching
Mike Modano's line against opponent's top offensive trio. Lehtinen
and Modano usually would outplay the opposition, but the absence of
Lehtinen has led Modano to wear down. ``I don't think at the end of
the day, without Lehtinen, (the strategy) has been very
productive,'' Hitchcock said. . . . Lehtinen, who was hoping to
come back a week ago, hasn't skated on his fractured right ankle
since Nov. 28 and is trying to rest it so it will heal completely.
He might be out until late December. . . .
</P>
<P>
   Detroit's Darren McCarty is undergoing experimental laser
treatment on his groin. If it fails, he will become the fourth Red
Wing in two years to have surgery for a lower-abdominal injury. . .
. Pat Verbeek is clicking with new Wing linemates Steve Yzerman and
Brendan Shanahan, recording seven points in a span of four games.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
