<P>
   RUSSIA-CHECHNYA _ MOSCOW _ The Russian government appeared to
ease a flee-or-die deadline Saturday for residents of the besieged
Chechen capital, Grozny, but vowed to pursue its punishing military
offensive in the breakaway republic despite intense international
criticism. (Holmes, Cox News Service) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   GORE-GA _ ATLANTA _ Vice President Al Gore, campaigning in
Georgia and Florida, participates in an African-American forum
Saturday morning in Atlanta before continuing on to central Florida
where he will address the Florida Democratic Convention in Orlando.
(Shepard, Cox News Service) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-FLA _ ORLANDO, Fla. _ President Clinton speaks to
Florida Democrats Saturday morning in what is likely to be his last
appearance at a state convention here. Clinton's success in the
1991 convention gave him the credibility he needed to win in 1992.
He also became the first president since Jimmy Carter to carry
Florida in 1996. Do they still love him? In the evening, President
Clinton goes to Fort Lauderdale where he will attend a fund-raiser
for Alcee Hastings. (Crowley, Palm Beach Post). 20.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   GORE-FLA _ ORLANDO, Fla. _ Al Gore campaigns at the convention
Saturday afternoon where he hopes to bring some life to his
struggling campaign. Gore, now an everyman, has many Florida
Democrats worried that if he becomes the nominee, he'll go down in
flames and take the Florida party with him. (Crowley, Palm Beach
Post). 20.
</P>
<P>
   POLITICAL-NOTES _ Mark Sherman's political notes. (Sherman,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   MEAT-ECOLI _ WASHINGTON _ The USDA's 'science-based' inspection
system doesn't test for several strains of e. coli bacteria that
scientists with the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention now
say may cause half the e. coli illnesses in America. While food
safety efforts have focused on the infamous 0157:H7 strain that
killed two children in the Jack-In-The-Box outbreak in 1993, its
toxic cousins _ strains once found only overseas _ have begun
appearing here. ``I've been screaming about the non-0157 strains
for years and nobody listened,'' said the head of the Food Safety
Initiative at Tufts University. (Montgomery/Jaspin, Cox News
Service) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   AIR-FORCE-MEMORIAL _ WASHINGTON _ Rallying his troops by e-mail,
retired Marine Gen. Charles G. Cooper warns, ``we're in the assault
phase of this momentous battle.'' His foe: the United States Air
Force. The Air Force has won most of the early skirmishes, but ``we
are dug in and determined,'' said Cooper. The battle is over
control of a strategic Virginia ridge overlooking the Potomac
River. The Air Force chose this prime spot near the rows of somber
white crosses at Arlington National Cemetery to build a memorial.
But the Marine Corps charges that the site is too close to its
famed Iwo Jima Memorial. (Dart, Cox News Service). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: MOVED Monday.
</P>
<P>
   SCHOOL-VIOLENCE _ WASHINGTON _ Over all, are schools this year
reacting sensibly to the shootings last spring? Educators, law
enforcement officials, software and hardware vendors, public
officials, parent of a murdered child, and teacher who was shot
while shielding a student comment. (Mollison, Cox News Service).
WITH PHOTOS. MOVED
</P>
