Anderson. &QL; 
__ Sign Of The Times &QL; 
On the night Charles Barkley's career ended with a knee injury in
Philadelphia, 76ers point guard Allen Iverson was not even in the
arena.
</P>
<P>
   The Sixers' leading scorer and defending NBA scoring champion
called in sick Wednesday but felt somewhat better later in the
evening and went to TGI Friday's on City Avenue, an establishment
popular with many of the players.
</P>
<P>
   When Iverson arrived, the phone lines at a local sports-talk
radio station went wild.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm sorry the whole thing even happened,'' Iverson said. ``If
I had known it was going to have this type of response, I would
never have come out. I would have eaten a peanut butter and jelly
sandwich.'' &QL; 
__ Rumor of the Week &QL; 
The Knicks are the latest team with an inexplicable interest in
Lakers forward Glen Rice. The Knicks wouldn't mind dumping Charlie
Ward or Chris Childs but would probably have to send a marquee
player (Allan Houston, Marcus Camby) for Rice. &QL;
</P>
